latestIgtvVideos.title: Holiday Ham How To!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Our Heritage Breed, naturally uncured, spiral cut hams are like nothing you have ever tasted. The intramuscular fat marbling, natural cure and sweet honey glaze make for one of the best holiday ham experiences you have ever had. Our flavorful ham comes wrapped in foil with our signature glaze package so all you have to do is throw it in the oven, warm it to your desired temp and then pour over the glaze. Nothing will compare to the taste of this spiral sliced holiday ham - plus, it’ll be the simplest to prepare and enjoy.

On a sour note, we lost the most of our reviews (and some of them were straight-up legendary), so it’s time to bring the heat…contest time! 

Leave a review–the more creative, the better–and our founders will pick one lucky winner (and maybe a few others) to receive 15 packs of TB bacon! Here’s how to do it:

1️⃣ Tap a product you love (comment “REVIEW” and we’ll DM you the link!)

2️⃣ Scroll all the way down until you see “write a review”

3️⃣ Submit your review

4️⃣ We’ll reach out to the winner by email and feature the winning review on social (and maybe a few runner-ups). 

Rules: US residents, 18+ only. Ends 8/31/25 at 11:59 PM MST. Not sponsored by Meta/TikTok. Winner will be announced in the comments of this post and via email newsletter. Beware of scams—this is the only official Tender Belly account that will be DMing you for information.

*Tender Belly prize shall be equivalent to 15 packs of retail bacon, which will be awarded either as (15) coupons or as (15) retail packs of bacon, based on the winner’s location/product availability.

Off the grid. No phones. No luxuries. Just two best friends (since they were 6!), a canoe, and a week deep in the Quetico wilderness. Snow, rain, brutal portages, fire bans…you name it, they pushed through it. 

Erik, TB’s co-founder, said it was some of the hardest physical work they’ve ever done, and every second was worth it. Sleeping under the stars, fully unplugged, fully alive. And yeah... plenty of bacon.

That’s how it’s done! 

#backpacking #offthegrid #camping #wilderness #survival

Old-world flavor, modern-day masterpiece. 🥓🍻 Chef Anthony Alejandro crafted this dish with crispy Emmentaler cheese-stuffed Tender Belly bacon, warm German potato salad, pickled apples, and a mulled cider gastrique—all inspired by the kind of charcuterie you'd find in Europe and the simple thought: this bacon deserves a beer.⁠
